      "writtenOn": "2016-11-09T21:18:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is actually required by the caller. It took me some time to understand why. I need to update the method\u0027s comment.\n\nThe interface for read() is that the caller writes the maximum amount of data it is ready to read in its buffer, and receives on exit the real amount that was read. See ReadBuffer implementation.\n\nAlso, it is expected to block, then read as much data as possible, which is why blocking is true only if (count \u003d\u003d 0) above. I should probably add more comments to explain, this is a very subtle point.\n\nWithout this behaviour, nothing works properly (debugging was ... interesting).",
